text:
Christopher Street, north side, east of, a point east of Seventh Avenue, as viewed from Grove Street (east side of this open area).

In the center is Waverly Place, and the Northern Dispensary. The spired structure in the background is Jefferson Market Court.

1895

J. J. Corell
P. L. Sperr

(1)
Seventh Ave., west side, north from and including Christopher Street. The Greenwich Village Theatre is at the right.
March 7, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, a year later. The sign "Irish Theatre" on the Greenwich Village Theatre refers to the company playing there at the time.
February 11, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, three years later. During the interval the Greenwich Village Theatre has been demolished and its site is now occupied by Stewarts Cafeteria, in a short time it will become the Willow Cafeteria.
May 1, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
